-- U.S. Population Rises to 308.7 Million, a 9.7% Gain From 2000, Census Says
-- B y   T i m o t h y   H o m a n
-- 2010-12-21T16:24:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-21/u-s-population-rises-to-308-7-million-a-9-7-gain-from-2000-census-says.html
The population in the U.S. grew to
308.7 million in 2010, from 281.4 million in 2000, the Census
Bureau said today in Washington.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Timothy Homan in Washington at 
